e mutability**\\\\n\\\\nI’m considering the challenges of mutating a public final static field in a native image. It seems like using `Unsafe.objectFieldOffset` might lead to errors with static finals, especially if they're build-time initialized. Reflection might not be a viable alternative here, either. Plus, there's the context of Native Image on Linux, and JNA could have its own substitutions. Overall, I think the hack could introduce some problematic scenarios.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_ypDFjywcgC5mdIf1W9lOktxH|fc_0fb63b68099e23620169f9031a6ac8819ca4bfcef7b69f63b4\", \"name\": \"edit\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/net.java.dev.jna/jna-platform/5.3.1/src/test/java/net_java_dev_jna/jna_platform/ConvertTest.java\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"import com.sun.jna.platform.win32.COM.util.IComEnum;\\nimport com.sun.jna.platform.win32.Variant;\\nimport com.sun.jna.platform.win32.Variant.VARIANT;\\nimport com.sun.jna.ptr.IntByReference;\\nimport java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException;\\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\\n\", \"newText\": \"import com.sun.jna.Native;\\nimport com.sun.jna.platform.win32.COM.util.IComEnum;\\nimport com.sun.jna.platform.win32.Variant;\\nimport com.sun.jna.platform.win32.Variant.VARIANT;\\nimport com.sun.jna.ptr.IntByReference;\\nimport java.lang.reflect.Field;\\nimport java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException;\\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\\nimport sun.misc.Unsafe;\\n\"}, {\"oldText\": \"        try {\\n            VARIANT variant = invokeConvertToVariant(value);\\n\\n            assertThat(variant.getVarType().intValue()).isEqualTo(Variant.VT_INT | Variant.VT_BYREF);\\n            assertThat(variant.getValue()).isInstanceOf(IntByReference.class);\\n            assertThat(((IntByReference) variant.getValue()).getValue()).isEqualTo(123);\\n        } catch (ExceptionInInitializerError error) {\\n            assertThat(rootCause(error).getMessage()).contains(\\\"Unsupported size: 16\\\");\\n     